fr.pinguet62.jsfring.gui.component.filter.operator

Interface Operator<Exp extends com.mysema.query.types.expr.SimpleExpression<T>,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    Exp - The type of SimpleExpression on which operator will be applied.
    T - The type of parameters.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NumberOperator<T>, StringOperator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BetweenOperator, ContainsOperator, EndsWithOperator, EqualsToOperator, GreaterThanOperator, IsNullOperator, LessThanOperator, LikeOperator, StartsWithOperator

    public interface Operator<Exp extends com.mysema.query.types.expr.SimpleExpression<T>,T>
extends Serializable
    The implementation must:
    • have a default constructor: the OperatorConverter use reflection to create new Operators;
    • Override Object.equals(Object) method: JSF component like SelectOneMenu use this method to check if the value is in the List).

      • apply

        com.mysema.query.types.Predicate apply(Exp path,
                                       T arg1,
                                       T arg2)
        Apply the Operator on path, with parameters (if required), and generate the BooleanExpression.
        Parameters:
        path - The SimpleExpression on which apply the operator.
        arg1 - The first parameter of operator.
        Ignored if the operator doesn't take parameter.
        arg2 - The second parameter of operator.
        Ignored if the operator take only 1 parameter.
        Returns:
        The where cause to apply for filtering.
